<!--312-->Cave Troll of Moria, Scourge of the Black Pit x 2<br />
<!--313-->Cave Troll&#39;s Hammer x 1<br />
<!--958-->Cave Troll&#39;s Chain x 1<br />
<!--77-->Goblin Spear x 1    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The deck is called &quot;Fastest gun in the West&quot; because of its fast card drawing ability.It draws cards in all the game phases: Fellowship (Gandalf, Elrond, Ottar, having in mind the rule of 4, of course), Shadow (Goblin Scimitars, Relics of Moria and They Are Coming), and even Manuever, Archery, Skirmish and Regroup (with Plundered Armories, if an orc with scimitar is killed, the scimitar is just passed to another orc and a card is drawn).<br />
The deck is huge (55 fellowship and 55 shadow cards), but with 4 Elronds, 3 Ottars, 4 x They Are Coming, 2 Gwemegils, starting Gandalf TGP, 4 Goblin Scimitars and 2 Plundered Armories it will be able to cycle pretty fast. <br />
The Cave Troll with his Hammer and Chain (usually fetched via Relics) and with the help of Dark Places will be able to do some major damage. Dark Places is also very useful to play Cavern Entrance, where the opponent&#39;s fellowship can easily be sent to meet his maker :).<br />
There is not much to be said about the fellowship, it is designed to draw and single-move, trying to stay alive and using all the fellowship cards, setting up the black hand and letting the Shadow side do its thing. Elrond heals himself and Ottar, Galadriel (usually) heals Elrond, just watch out for the Tower Assassins.<br />
And BTW, the deck has only 3 cultures, so CC can do nothing but be overwhelmed by somebody.<br />
Key cards:<br />
Gandalf, Elrond, Ottar - everybody knows the power of this combo. Draw, draw, draw.<br />
Galadriel LOTGW - Heals Elrond.<br />
Celeborn - use him to heal Elrond<br />
Gwemegil - a great way to reconcile your hand and prepare for the Shadow Phase<br />
They Are Coming, Goblin Scimitar - Everybody playing Moria appreciates the power of these cards<br />
Relics of Moria, Plundered Armories - to play scimitars and Troll&#39;s weapons (Relics only) from the discard pile.<br />
Have fun! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
